public abstract class DFSDistanceLabeler<V,E>
extends java.lang.Object

Depth-first search (DFS) is an algorithm for traversing or searching tree or graph data structures. One starts at the root (selecting some node as the root in the graph case) and explores as far as possible along each branch before backtracking. The asymptotic order of DFS is O( V + E ). References:

  • Thomas H. Cormen, Clifford Stein, Ronald L. Rivest, and Charles E. Leiserson. 2001. Introduction to Algorithms (2nd ed.). McGraw-Hill Higher Education. pp. 540-549.
